-- Indian central bank to defer auction of $2.4 bln in govt bonds 
-- By Sumeet Chatterjee
-- Mon Jan 13, 2014 09:27AM EST
-- None



MUMBAI, Jan 13 (Reuters) - India's central bank said on Monday a decision has been taken to defer the auction of federal government bonds worth 150 billion rupees ($2.42 billion) scheduled to be held on Jan. 17 on review of the government's cash position and funding requirement.

The Reserve Bank of India statement did not give details.